name: Mary Tubbs
text: IF I could have given ZERO stars, I would have.. I HAD to leave at least ONE star to leave this review......isn’t Christianity about love and forgiveness..? Isn’t it about bein a true Godly person and doing things for ANYONE, even those who stray..? Things that God in return blesses you for..? If you go against everything you “believe” and have the nerve to stand in that church preaching about and daring to teach OTHERS, because your OWN family has made bad choices and done things you don’t approve of, THEN YOU REALLY NEED TO BE IN A DIFFERENT BUSINESS, or do some soul searching..!! I’m human..I err..I sin..DAILY..! And I repent where I feel conviction..but I’d NEVER put MY FAMILY MEMEBER, (or yours, rather..i.e. Bradley Dodd) out in the cold or expect him to sleep outside in the rain or freezing cold with the dogs, just because I may be embarrassed about what others may think of me helping the “black sheep” of my FAMILY..! Even when OTHERS in your life have been forgiven.. OTHERS that younstill lay with daily..? What about THEIR a indiscretions..? You get to pick and choose who you forgive and tear down..? And a man that wondered into your life gets such, but the fruit of your loin doesn’t get the same treatment..? Yes, I’d be praying..and I’ll be praying..for you hypocritical, double standard, hell bound human beings..! There IS a church I’ll be checkin with to help Bradley..with folks who REALLY care because they are human too, and know that ANYTHING can be forgiven, especially stupid decisions AS A CHILD..even the way you all do your own legacy..! God sees all..and he knows the truths of the heart, regardless of which face you wear that day....

name: Eric Watson
text:
The pastor here preaches on scripture, not his own opinion.  He follows the Bible soundly and explains it in a way that is both easy to understand and in a deeply meaningful way that will make you sit back and reflect on the word of God.

The people here don't judge you.  They are open, friendly, and welcoming.  This is my favorite place in Tallassee to fellowship and learn about Christ!!!

name: Rachel Wingler
text: First Baptist Church is  a "Grace Place." It's a great place to learn from Biblical teaching, connect with great people of any age, and get involved in a community of people who understand that we are all recovering sinners with all sorts of backgrounds and all kinds of futures. Come as you are, however casual or formal you may be. With preschool, children's, youth, college, adult, and senior adult classes to choose from, you're sure to find a place to fit any stage of your life. The teaching available at every age and level is great, both in services and in small groups. It's grounded and understandable from preschool to senior adults. The worship style varies from southern gospel to hymns to current popular worship music. A normal service consists of singing, prayer, and teaching/studying of the Bible. There's a place for everyone here, and we'd love to have you! I found family, love, and grace here, and I hope you do, too.

name: Julie Reynolds
text:
Things you can expect at First Baptist:
1. There are two morning worship services and two Sunday school hours. You can go to Sunday school at 8:45 and then worship at 10 or do it the other way around.
2. Dress is casual, but people come dressed in all levels on the scale of informal to formal.
3. The music style is blended, leaning contemporary
4. Sunday School is very important to the overall experience at First Baptist. You get the family feeling in Sunday School and the feeling you are part of something bigger than yourself in the worship services. Adults will have more than one class to choose from; so, people try several classes until they find the one that fits them.

name: Jim Bearrentine
text: My wife and I were looking for a Bible based church where our whole family could grow.  After moving to the area we visited First Baptist.  The preschool is wonderful. There are activities for young children and teens, and there are many adult classes to choose from.  The pastor provides excellent Biblical guidance during the worship service. This energizes us and motivates us throughout the week. The Sunday School class provides opportunities to discuss real-life situations through a Christian perspective.  Most importantly, we feel that First Baptist is a place where our spiritual needs are met so that we can grow stronger in Christ, and from that we are challenged to go out and serve in the community and to meet the needs of others.

name: Brantley Chandler
text: First Baptist Church is very open and welcoming. There are people by the front door ready to shake your hand and give you a program when you walk in. The members enjoy meeting new people and helping them in any way they can. There are Sunday School classes for every age group and the classes are small making it easier to get to know new people and have a more personal relationship. First Baptist Tallassee is a very family friendly environment at the church there is a preschool wing for bed babies through 5, a children's wing for kindergarten through 6th grade, and a youth group for 7th through 12th. At First Baptist we have 6 main goals they are Christ centered worship, biblical instruction, prayer, world evangelization, nurturing fellowship, and caring acts. These goals are intended to grow Christians as individuals, as brothers and sisters in Christ, and to spread the gospel not only in Tallassee, Al but to the world.

name: Sharon Pride
text:
Nice church. Great daycare and preschool! My daughter attended preschool there from age 2 through K4. Tuition can be pricey & there can be a waiting list from time to time, but my husband & I believe it was worth it. The administration & staff are both knowledgeable & experienced. Admission to the preschool/daycare/after school care is limited. You either have to be buzzed in by staff or you have to have a security code to unlock the door. Children must be both signed in & out. Children are supervised at all times. Meals are nutritious & made on site by some truly wonderful ladies. Children are educated, cared for & loved by administrator & staff. We feel that our daughter's 3 years at FBCHPS has benefitted her educationally, socially & morally. She is 8 years old now & has been away from the preschool since she was 5 & what memories she has of her time there are precious to her. She misses it❤️

Although neither my husband nor I are members of FBCH, we have attended services there several times. We found the congregation & minister to be welcoming & warm. Congregants are kind & generous. There is ample parking for both the disabled & non. The church is wheelchair accessible & congregants are cheerful & helpful. This is a Community Oriented church. By that, I mean that the church & congregation are highly supportive of the Headland community & the schools of the City of Headland. I found the congregation & the staff of the preschool to be open, helpful & compassionate to the needs of members of the community once they were advised of needs. Very good people doing very good work for the Lord ⛪🏫🙏💕

name: saleen mustang
text:
First, the phrase "come as you are" is intended to combat the false belief that we must make ourselves acceptable to Christ by ceasing from sin or doing good deeds before coming to Him. This we cannot do and could not be further from the truth. In fact, it is the exact opposite of Christ's teaching. Scripture tells us that our good deeds cannot save us (Ephesians 2:8–9). Even our best works are as filthy rags when viewed by our holy God (Isaiah 64:6). If we could make ourselves righteous before coming to Christ then His sacrificial, substitutionary death would not have been necessary for our salvation. Christ Himself stated that He came to save sinners (Matthew 9:12–13). He ate and drink with sinners (Matthew 9:10). He protected sinners, such as the woman caught in adultery, from the self-righteous Pharisees (John 8:3–11). He did not come to save those who in their sinful pride believe themselves to be righteous, but those who know they are not righteous. Jesus calls all who are weary and burdened by their sin to come to Him and find rest for their souls in Him (Matthew 11:28–30). He calls not just sinners but the foremost of sinners to come to Him (1 Timothy 1:15–16).

So, does Jesus demands anything from those who would come to Him? Yes, He demands that we be born again spiritually (John 3:1–8). It is not enough to make moral improvements, we need new hearts (Ezekiel 36:26), hearts that are repentant and believing. God commands all people to repent and believe in Jesus Christ in order to be saved (Mark 1:15; Acts 19:4; 20:21; Hebrews 6:1). However, even this repentance and faith are not our own doing but are gifts from God through which we receive the salvation that is found in Jesus Christ (Ephesians 2:8–9).

As a result of being made alive to God and becoming new creations in Christ, our lives begin to change (Colossians 2:13; 2 Corinthians 5:17). Although we do not become sinless after this rebirth, we do have a different mindset toward sin. We desire to depart from sin, we mourn over our remaining sin, we are convicted by the Holy Spirit when we do sin, and we confess our sin to God (2 Timothy 2:19; Romans 7:24; John 16:8; 1 John 1:9). After our spiritual rebirth, we also begin to exhibit the fruit of the Holy Spirit, such as love, joy, and peace (Galatians 5:22–23). However, all this is a result of coming to Christ and not a precondition for coming to Him. We come as we are, but we do not remain as we were (Philippians 1:6; Romans 12:1–2; 2 Corinthians 3:18).

Let all who are thirsty come and drink from the Living Water, Jesus Christ (John 4:10; 7:38).

name: Frog Price
text:
Romar Beach Baptist Church is a blessing to our family that brings a welcome calm to our beach expeditions and travels. We loved the people that we met. Most were visitors as this church has only to or three dozen members with 200 or so visitors each week.

The staff was warm and welcoming. The volunteers were so upbeat about the service and just full of information about the congregation.  The Sr. Pastor, Rev. Fowler, was just the sweetest old leprechaun looking fossile we ever did meet. He was quick with a smile, a wink and a kind word. His wife, Jane, is in charge of the children at the service. She is a precious and wonderful sweet lady. She was quick with a hug too.
All in all.... this is the most beautiful, God fearing, Bible teaching place we've ever been.

name: Blake Jessup
text:
At perhaps the lowest point in my life I sought refuge and sanctuary here so I could pray and reflect. It was 7m on May 29 and the church was closed, yet when I called a woman answered and invited me in around back. She introduced me to Pastor Morris who read well my hearts cares and concerns and sat with me and talked of the heart's resolve and God presence guiding us through life’s trials. I was there for a couple hours and in our last conversation he asked “Well blake let me ask you again since you can’t backtrack (because life won’t allow you to go back the way you came), where you headed?” I thought he was talking about geography and it wasn’t until July that he’d been talking about the direction of my life and the condition of my soul.

I’ve prayed several times a day since then and have taught biblical passages as English Literature lessons. Where am I headed? Back to Montgomery and Pastor Morris  to  surrender my life and soul to Christ this Sunday July 21, 2019

name: Amanda Green
text: The elders are old school!  My generation was the last to be born and come of age in the 20th Century.  As a result we came into existence of multiple generations.  The "Hippies" we're our parents.  Our Aunts and Uncles were Vietnam Veterans and our Grandparents were WW2 Survivors and children of sharecroppets and first generation emacipated descendendants of slaves and immigrant families.  We all of course had Native American ideology and DNA famial background history (live off the land w/out government assistance if land and natural resources was made available to do so bc God would and does supply our every need). This mix blood/ multiple generational blessing created mixed up ideologies.  This ideology is what causes me to love this church and it's elders!  I can rely on them to keep the doors open, a preacher in the pulpit and someone who knows my name even if I have been M.I.A. for a while.  In this church God is worshipped and through his blessings and strength my elders hold down the fort while the younger generations interact/grow/clash/fight/return wounded from the battle feild called "life".  If I am blessed/privaledged enough I hope one day I am a elder who makes sure no matter what the war/pandemic/life phase the youth are engaged in they know on Sunday and Wednesday their is a safe place/space/ word that they can retreat too and rest and rehabilitate while they lick their physical/emotional/and spiritual wounds so they can heal to awaken and face another day in their journey called life.  This is why I love my home church!  I give God all the glory and gratitude but it is my elders and their steadfast belief in the bible and our traditions/beliefs that keep me a member and coming back when I need a safe place to relax and trust the old ways and most important God and his son Jesus Christ! are real!  This is my home church and my place of worship!  I love this church through thick and thin don't judge it just concentrate on God and the traditional hymns!   If you do you will end your day rested, relaxed and spirituality renewed!  You will  awaken the next day prepared to do what is necessary to preserve our country,  yourself, our beliefs, our community, our families and traditions and by doing the acts of preservation you prove the existence and eternal power of our Father God in heaven and his son Jesus Christ!  How I must ask can anyone ask anything else of a place of worship?   This is my home church and I give it all the stars the internet can offer!

name: bogster76
text:
Our family moved to Huntsville in the summer of 2017 and we visited this church while looking for a home church.
While this church is not where we settled, I can honestly say it was the BEST sermon I heard in this area. I still listen to Pastor Blair’s expository preaching online and I love his commitment to the truth of God’s word and how he explains difficult passages with so much clarity. I find his teaching very thorough, challenging and humble.
The fact that he doesn’t use the KJV was a huge plus for me ( someone mentioned it as a negative) because I truly believe there are more accurate translations out there than the KJV.

( disclosure about why we settled on another church: our family is a family of 5 and we simply have different needs and personalities so another church in the area came in first place when we all voted. That being said, our impression was that Providence Baptist is also a wonderful, God-honoring church.)

name: Ric Crooks
text: Providence Baptist Church (PBC) is a traditional, God-centered Reformed Baptist church.  PBC aligns itself with the 1689 LBCF; and centers on making and training disciples in God's word, stirring one another up to love and good works, and actively supporting missions.  I equate their adult Sunday School classes to seminary-style classes, with different levels based upon your current understanding of various Biblical truths.  The children's and youth classes are focused on teaching Scripture in a God-centered way.  The Worship Service follows the regulative principle of worship (prayer, singing [from hymnals], reading Scripture, expository preaching, and administering the ordinances).  It is a wonderful place to worship God alongside His people!

name: Conrad Burford (Rebel)
text: I am always apprehensive about attending a large church. I'm usually a smaller church type person. I will admit that for a large church that it greatly surprised me. There is a very strong sense of community here. Everyone that I have met here are all greatly involved in the church and all of its wonderful ministries. The performance by the First Baptist Church Choir is completely amazing. I love to sing at church, but this was different. I found it so beautiful that I caught myself just wanting to listen and enjoy the peace it brought to me hear God being praised so amazingly and beautifully. The Sunday School classes that they offer here covers any preference that you can imagine from the children's classes all the way to the various adult classes as well. I was very, very grateful that the lessons covered by their classes teaches the same criteria to children, in their own understanding, as well as it teaches the adults. That is a togetherness unrivaled by my experiences up til now. Like I previously stated, at First Baptist Church everyone is on the same page so to speak. I love learning about God. This is a great place to gain more knowledge about "The Rock" in my life. This is a true home for building on and creating the perfect foundation.

name: Christopher Finch
text:
Crosspoint started off as a satellite location of the First Baptist Church of Center Point. After over 100 years, FBCCP has now closed its historic location, selling to a different ministry.

Having said that, Crosspoint carries many of the members that used to attend FBCCP.

What I like about Crosspoint is the Trail Life scouting program that the church sponsors with Troop 242. Trail Life is what scouting used to be, for those of us that remember.

If you are looking to get your son into scouting that teaches not only camping, outdoors, and life skills, but also has the moral aptitude to it, then look no further!

text:
The first time I stepped thru the doors of this church, I felt at home. It was my first step in visiting around due to a church closing. I had felt so unsettled & had prayed for Gods guidance & to feel i belonged. I couldn’t seem to find a desire to go anywhere else so I continued to pray for God to lead me to my new family.
A month later I continued to visit until I felt God tell me this was where He meant for me to be & this was my new church family. There was nothing I didn’t love about my decision to join.
I am so grateful to God for His faithfulness & His guidance,not only for me but for my brother, my sister & brother in law & my neighbor of 48 yrs. We all feel so blessed to be a part of this church family & our Pastor Bro Daniel DeLaney & his family. We would love for anyone who doesn’t have a home church to come visit.
God will bless you in so many ways.

They have moved locations since i attended and when i came back to Huntsville to visit my folks i thought the church had folded but then i saw a commercial with Pastor Allison and i looked him up and found the new location of the church.  I have not attended the church in many years but have listened to his sermons that are on his churches website and he has not lost his hard style of preaching one bit.  I love it!!!! Great church! Not sure about the negative comments. Notice that there are no specifics, just accusations. Beware of baseless accusations!

No church is perfect, including MDC (it has people, and people aren't perfect), but if you're looking for a church where you can learn about God in a setting designed for worship, you'll fit right in.

Oh, and no, I'm not a member there and I wasn't asked by anyone at the church to give this review. My comments come from my own experience while visiting.

text: Why do you not have a Statement of Faith on your website? Why do you not allow women to wear slacks to church? We are no  longer under the Law, but under Grace. Women are to dress modestly, but it does not say they are not to wear slacks, that is a "yoke" that your church is putting around the neck of the women. Jesus came to set us FREE! Galations 5:1 "For freedom Christ has set us FREE, stand firm therefore, and DO NOT SUBMIT AGAIN TO A 'YOKE' OF SLAVERY" 1 Timothy 3:9"I also want the women to dress "modestly", with "decency" and Propriety.........continue and you will see dressing in slacks is not mentioned!! You are once again "oppressing" people by your man made rules and regulations, just like the Catholic's and other false religions. You tell your congregation that they can not take Communion on Sunday April 3, 2016 because they are spreading "rumors" about a "Brother" in the church, the same "Brother" that you took away his position in the church due to the "rumors". You have no authority to stop a Christian from taking Communion!! They are to confess their sins to God before partaking of it, but you have no authority to stop them. This is a church Legalism.If righteousness comes through the Law, then Christ died needlessly. Jesus hates Legalism because it does not deal with the condition of the "heart". Luke 11:37-54......do you not know the Bible??

name: Tammy Fiscus
text:
Love this church. I have been a member there for 16 years now.  Preaching is sound doctrine and full of love. Salvation is through the grace of God. As for the preaching on Sunday April 3rd, I am sorry you, as a visitor, had to hear that message. The preaching was not aimed at the brother in Christ like you thought, it was to those busy bodies that like to spread gossip. Pastor Allison was correct in holding it off for a bit so we have a right as a church to get right with God. The Lord's supper is not something to be taking lightly. Some Corinthians died when they took of the Lord's supper unworthily. Pastor was watching for his flock at the time.
Yes we are free from the law as far as Salvation is concerned however we are still to obey God to have a close walk with Him. God tells us that if we love Him we will obey Him. As for women wearing slacks, we do not stand at the door telling anyone they can't come in because they are wearing pants. However in the new testament it tells women they are to be adorned in modest apparel. It says women are not to wear that which pertaineth to a man. Pants used to be called Britches. The men wore linen britches in the Bible times. Therefore, pants pertain to men not women. Women didn't wear pants until World war 2, when women went to work to help out.
Yes we use the KJV of the Bible. It was the one that was transcribed from the original text. It has no flaws it is God's word for the english language.
I am sorry that you had a bad experience coming to our church. I support my church and my pastor.
Just a side note though, let's say you have a child and that child is fixing to run into the street. You see the car coming your child does not.  Do you not warn that child by yelling "GET OUT OF THE ROAD"?  Of course you do. Why? Don't you love that child?  Yes you do. You tell your children and punish your child because you love them and you know the dangers that lie ahead. That is what a overseer does.  God gave us at MBC pastor Allison and he is our overseer for our spiritual well being. He is to correct us when we are doing wrong.
As far as the brother you were talking about, we as a church are praying for him and his family.

text: I was in a predicament today and that I fully believe Satan's demons worked their hardest and gave it their best shot to get me to go back to the old sinful that I once was. I don't want to sound like I am praising man but at the same time I want others to understand how God uses men of God to give us examples of how we should I act and conduct our own lives. I really don't know how because I do not have a vehicle and live pretty good distance from Lakewood however I know this Sunday morning where I want to be and pretty much no then meat, not the milk, that I will be given there. I know this I know myself I am asking and will continue to ask the Lord to provide some way for me to be there on Sunday morning. There's no way I could walk that far however if the Lord show me someone with the bicycle, i would ride it to be there on Sunday. name: nadine maxwell
text: This church has a family friendly atmosphere where the worship experience is always spiritual. This is a historical church that has been very active in the Civil Rights Movement. Our church family is always actively engaging our youth and young adults with a variety of Faith building activities such as; Vacation Bible School, trips to the museum in Montgomery or Birmingham, Six Flag trip, Movie Night, Praise Dancing,  Children's Church, Easter & Christmas Programs,  Youth Awards and Recognition Day, Praise and Worship Choirs, Missionary Society Circles, Deacon Wives, Fishers of Men and the Brotherhood Ministry...just to name a few. The 17th Street Missionary Baptist Church is celebrating 139 years of Proclaiming God's Holy Word and Awesome Greatness, the fourth Sunday in August. We are also having Revival on 22nd and 23rd of August 7pm nightly. Come join us as we  lift up the Name of Jesus, For He is Always Worthy to be Praised!!!

text: Hey Gary, I spent last evening with what looked to be around 1000 of my very best friends sitting in the parking lot of your church.  Such a warm and respectful crowd, lots of little children and qutie a few old codgers like me.  I commend you and your church for allowing folks to gather there outside of official church times.  So many congregations today would worry about damage, to the facilities or to the reputation of the church, forgetting that church is not a building it is a people and the highest calling of the people is that they open their hearts and their homes to the stranger. Please pass my love and appreciation along to your congregation for such a wonderful place to look up into the sky with wonder.

I visit my sister Anne Posey who is a member if Sunview Baptist. I go to church with her and my nephew Keith Posey faithfully. The past 3 months ( March,April, and May ) I have gone to many churches in my past but I just knew God sent me here cause this is the one where I belong. He knew if any pastor and Sunday school teacher could reach me... It would Chris our senior Sunday school teacher and Pastor Brother Mark Boyd. I am going to share an experience that happened to me one Sunday. Chris was teaching class and as soon as he started talking he caught my full attention that day.... never in many years has that happened to me!! I mean my mind didn't even stray for a second!! Then we were in church for our daily service... boy... can Brother Mark touch a soul...cause that day he really drew me into his God.  We sang a song Lift Up The Cross... oh what a touching heart felt song. Again Brother Mark caught my attention and I wouldn't astray from him. at the end of the sermon as we stood for those to come forward i felt a coldness run through my body as I then felt like I was dizzy,  light headed of course I got scared and started praying dear Lord please make this feeling go away...well it didn't my heart started beating fast due to anxiety built up I was starting to turn to my sister and tell het how I was feeling and needed to step out. But, out of no where a warm sensation went up my stomach through my chest and out of nowhere this most beautiful sensation went through me and I felt such a peacefulness and contentment within me. It wasn't until we left to go for lunch afterwards that started crying cause that was an experience I have never had. I told my sister about it and she said the Lord Jesus came into my soul. Let me tell you something... I will never forget that beautiful moment. For I will take it to the gave with me. This is not a made up story it really happened to me. I  finally talked to Brother Mark about my experience and he was amazing in helping me understand the Holy Spirit touched my soul that Sunday.He took the time to sit down with me and even read some verses from the bible to help me understand. so now I am no longer frightened if what I experienced that wonderful,day.
Thank you Brother Mark and Chris
I can't wait to visit again to see all of you. My friends, my church, my Godly home. The people there make you feel welcomed and make you feel like you belong. And that's not fake either just love them all to pieces. I want to thank my sister for bringing and introducing me to her Christian family.
May God bless all and everyone of you.

name: James Smith
text:
My wife and I visited this church four or five times this year. The first time we visited the pastor read a verse and told us a story about a cornfield. He then told us about his old church and how great it was. The church had about 40-50 people there and it was a good mix of ages.

The next time the teenagers led the service and the church was alive and full of energy. It was a very moving and touching service. The church was overflowing with people and looked very alive.

We went back a third time and it was the pastor preaching again. He was back to reading a verse and telling stories. This time it was about being tricked into drinking alcohol. He went on to tell how great his old church was. The church didn’t look the same as the previous times. There were fewer people and noticeably the younger people were gone.

We visited one more time and a few weeks back. Same old preacher but the most surprising thing was nobody was there. I think there was around 20 people there and nobody younger than me.

I don’t know what happened to this church but I can tell you if you visit the pastors old church it’s filled with more life than this one. This one feels like it’s on its last leg. Everyone is over 50 and the pastor seems to be stuck in the past. Especially on his “old church”

THANK YOU First Baptist for taking a stand, for standing up for your beliefs and principles.  More of us in this country need to do so.

name: Anonymous
text: The red flags were obvious to anyone to see early on; you pretty much had to not want to see it to not see it. There was a reason hoardes of deacons and committee chairs and Sunday school teachers left; there was a reason the church couldn't keep a worship leader, a youth pastor, or a children's pastor. At least two current deacons were warned, as long as five years ago, about specific character concerns and about the way the leadership of the church was being structured, but anyone raising concerns was shamed into silence/out the door. That's what happens when you put bibilically unqualified leaders in charge who care only about being in charge and run off the good leaders. That's how a corrupt pastor builds an army of undyingly loyal yes men and insulates himself from any accountability. It makes me sick the number of good men and women that got railroaded, humiliated, and in some instances slandered, for the sake of a man (two really) who was never working for the church's interests but for his own. That church owes a public apology to a lot of people, but it will never come. Unfortunately I don't see much hope for this church ever recovering because the same people who enabled the last pastor will get to pick the next one. Rinse and repeat.

name: Cory Leckrone
text:
We are a military family and just moved into Deer Creek and instantly began searching for churches to attend. We drove by Thorington Road Baptist Church on our way in and out of our house and decided to give it a try. Additionally, they were hosting a VBS that week as well which caught our attention and we signed our 5 year old up for it.

First Impression: This congregation is friendly, welcoming and caring. We felt very welcomed here. We were directed to the kids area to drop off our children before service, and introduced to the childrens leader. Once we arrived in the auditorium, seveal people came up and introduced themselves to us and told us they were glad we were there including Pastor Michael Trull. This church feels very much like a family and you can tell that from the first instance you walk in.

The service was great, the worship music had a good balance of newer songs and older hymns, the message was relevant and the gospel was clearly presented.

The VBS lasted from Sunday-Thursday and our 5 year old had a blast. You could tell the church congregation invested a lot of time and energy in preparing for VBS from decorations, to lessons, to crafts, etc. They did an amazing job! Kudos to the volunteers/church members.

If you are looking for a good bible preaching church in the East Montgomery area make sure to check this one out.

text: The pastor is great however the church felt very much like a clique :(. The pastor preached very well but again the people, to me, were not friendly and I felt a little out of place. I would say if you have gone there since the beginning that you will love it but to someone "new" I did not feel welcome. I hate to say that but maybe this review will benefit someone else and/or help the church family to see how they are making others feel while being a visitor there. Thanks.

resp.text:
We are so sorry for your experience at North Valley Church.  There is no excuse for a person not feeling loved and welcomed.  We will continue to improve so that others may not share your negative experience.  We are human, and sometimes fail.  Please accept our apologies.

I would be honored to sit down with you in person, buy you a meal, and listen to any other concerns.  We thank you for your honesty.  May God bless you in your walk with Jesus Christ, our Savior.  Pastor Chris Crain, NVC

Never in classroom at pickup the board outisde the room would say where they were supposed to be but they were never there. I always had to track my child down who would be with teachers I've never met. I could of taken anyone's child home. Came home with bite marks and diaper rash, dirty face and hands. name: Cornelia Farm
text:
If you are looking for a church to make you feel warm & fuzzy without knowing and applying the Word, look elsewhere. 12th Street Baptist is a family of believers who are striving together to hold ourselves accountable to God and his Word and to live out our faith in our day-to-day lives. This means taking hard looks at our opinions and biases and taking everything back to Scripture, where there are many uncomfortable yet necessary truths. We are always found wanting when we compare ourselves to God’s standard, but the Good News is that the grace of Jesus covers us as we are sanctified every day in our relationship with Him.

We are an intentional church. Here, we get into theology; we ask hard questions; we dive into the nitty-gritty details of life and we apply what we’ve learned about God to our daily lives and relationships. Is it hard? Yes. Is it sometimes uncomfortable? Absolutely. But the point of our faith is not to be comfortable. It is to know the Truth and to lovingly live it out with the help and grace of Jesus Christ. And it is WORTH IT.

If that’s not what you want, all the best to you in your search. But if you want a family of fellow sinners saved by grace who are all struggling together, held together by our faith and taking everything back to the Cross, then this may be the family for you.

name: Russ Jacks
text:
I grew up as a Southern Baptist, and over the past 40 years as a Christ follower, and as someone who has been to many, many, many, churches, (Baptist, Church of Christ, and Presbyterian) across the United States and visiting churches across the world as a US Marine. All I can say is this, having lived in the South in the USA, and also traveling across the world as a Marine. Having listened to the best Baptist Pastors in the USA, I have never heard a  better pastor or speaker of the “Word” than the current pastor of Mount Joy Baptist church in Jasper AL. If you want a Bible-based ministry, with honest people, and honest biblical teachings, then you WILL NOT FIND A BETTER  church than Mount Joy Baptist Church!

This is coming from someone who has been a doubter and believer in the WORD.

This Church and this Pastor have restored my faith in GOD, and the truth of God’s Word!!

Plus, I really love the architecture of this Church. It is simple, but incredibly well laid out and has very good materials. Whoever built this Church was a person of detail.
